WEBVTT

00:00:00.896 --> 00:00:05.359 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our disciple-making work
is a weighty assignment from Jehovah.

00:00:05.359 --> 00:00:09.405 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But he does not expect us
to accomplish it on our own.

00:00:09.405 --> 00:00:13.451 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are you making full use
of the help Jehovah provides?

00:00:13.451 --> 00:00:18.456 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We know that you will be encouraged
by the following three-part symposium.

00:00:18.456 --> 00:00:22.001 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Each speaker
will introduce the one to follow.

00:00:22.001 --> 00:00:25.671 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Robert Ciranko,
a helper to the Writing Committee,

00:00:25.671 --> 00:00:28.174 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
will deliver the first talk entitled

00:00:28.174 --> 00:00:31.260 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Experience the Joy of Disciple-Making

00:00:31.260 --> 00:00:35.264 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Accept Jehovah’s Help—
Research Tools.”

00:00:35.264 --> 00:00:38.643 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Ciranko, you have our full attention.

00:00:45.191 --> 00:00:47.193 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What would you say?

00:00:47.193 --> 00:00:50.530 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How important is the disciple-making work?

00:00:50.530 --> 00:00:55.201 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, it is so important
that Jehovah God is directly involved in it.

00:00:55.201 --> 00:00:57.203 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How do we know?

00:00:57.203 --> 00:01:01.958 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Turn in your Bibles, please,
to 1 Corinthians 3:9

00:01:01.958 --> 00:01:04.836 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—1 Corinthians 3:9.

00:01:04.836 --> 00:01:08.756 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It says: “For we are God’s fellow workers.

00:01:08.756 --> 00:01:13.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You are God’s field under cultivation,
God’s building.”

00:01:14.304 --> 00:01:16.639 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Just think what a privilege we have to share

00:01:16.639 --> 00:01:19.184 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with the almighty Creator of the universe

00:01:19.184 --> 00:01:22.896 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the work that he considers
so important here on earth.

00:01:22.896 --> 00:01:25.440 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He allows us to experience the joy

00:01:25.440 --> 00:01:29.819 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of helping to build people
into disciples of Jesus Christ.

00:01:30.945 --> 00:01:34.240 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We know from the verses
that come just before verse 9,

00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:37.619 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that while we plant
and water seeds of Kingdom truth

00:01:37.619 --> 00:01:39.996 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the hearts of interested ones,

00:01:39.996 --> 00:01:43.750 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah is the one
who makes those seeds grow.

00:01:43.750 --> 00:01:47.128 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
However, knowing this
should not minimize in our minds

00:01:47.128 --> 00:01:50.882 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the importance of our part
in the disciple-making work.

00:01:50.882 --> 00:01:54.219 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What we do and how we do it has an impact

00:01:54.219 --> 00:01:56.471 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
on how those seeds of truth will grow.

00:01:57.681 --> 00:02:01.643 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And Jehovah knows that the more skilled
we become at making disciples,

00:02:01.643 --> 00:02:04.521 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the more effective
we will be as his fellow workers,

00:02:04.521 --> 00:02:08.233 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the more enjoyable
the work will be for us.

00:02:08.233 --> 00:02:13.238 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
To that end, Jehovah equips
us to teach as effectively as possible.

00:02:13.238 --> 00:02:16.074 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All we have to do is accept his help.

00:02:16.074 --> 00:02:19.036 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And that is what this symposium is all about:

00:02:19.036 --> 00:02:23.206 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
learning to benefit
from the research tools Jehovah has given us,

00:02:23.206 --> 00:02:28.086 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the help that is available
from our brothers, and the power of prayer.

00:02:29.296 --> 00:02:32.174 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Each talk in this symposium
will consider two questions.

00:02:32.174 --> 00:02:35.928 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
First, what help has Jehovah given us?

00:02:35.928 --> 00:02:38.847 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And second, how can we use that help

00:02:38.847 --> 00:02:41.391 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to increase our joy in the ministry?

00:02:42.768 --> 00:02:45.938 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s start by talking about research tools.

00:02:45.938 --> 00:02:48.357 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What help has Jehovah given us?

00:02:48.357 --> 00:02:53.320 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He has given us the right tools
—the best tools—for our work.

00:02:53.320 --> 00:02:56.907 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Foremost of all,
he has dignified us by allowing us

00:02:56.907 --> 00:02:59.368 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to use his written Word, the Bible,

00:02:59.368 --> 00:03:02.413 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and that is our most important tool
for the ministry.

00:03:03.622 --> 00:03:08.294 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Turn to 2 Timothy 3:16, 17

00:03:08.294 --> 00:03:11.380 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—2 Timothy 3:16, 17.

00:03:12.548 --> 00:03:15.760 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It says: “All Scripture is inspired of God

00:03:15.760 --> 00:03:19.847 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and beneficial for teaching, for reproving,

00:03:19.847 --> 00:03:23.726 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“for setting things straight,
for disciplining in righteousness,

00:03:23.726 --> 00:03:28.731 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“so that the man of God
[or woman of God] may be fully competent,

00:03:28.731 --> 00:03:31.984 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
completely equipped for every good work.”

00:03:33.945 --> 00:03:37.448 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We should want to do all
we can to keep honing our skills

00:03:37.448 --> 00:03:41.994 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and using the Bible to teach the truth
about God, Christ, and the Kingdom.

00:03:42.954 --> 00:03:45.957 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the beauty of using
the Bible is that the message

00:03:45.957 --> 00:03:50.461 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
contained in it can literally change people.

00:03:50.461 --> 00:03:52.880 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Religious falsehoods and erroneous ideas

00:03:52.880 --> 00:03:56.467 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
have become “strongly entrenched”
in the minds of sincere people.

00:03:56.467 --> 00:03:58.803 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But the Bible, when used effectively,

00:03:58.803 --> 00:04:01.723 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
can overturn those wrong beliefs.

00:04:03.057 --> 00:04:05.351 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Why, the Bible
can even help a person understand

00:04:05.351 --> 00:04:08.313 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
his own deepest thoughts and feelings.

00:04:08.313 --> 00:04:13.109 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One Bible translation
renders that 16th verse by saying:

00:04:13.109 --> 00:04:18.114 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The Bible is useful for resetting
the direction of a man’s life.”

00:04:19.699 --> 00:04:21.826 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Through our own study of the Bible,

00:04:21.826 --> 00:04:25.788 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we can become skilled
at using the Scriptures in the ministry.

00:04:25.788 --> 00:04:30.335 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And to help us succeed in this, Jehovah
has given us a variety of research tools

00:04:30.335 --> 00:04:33.755 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to use in personal study and family worship.

00:04:33.755 --> 00:04:36.466 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
These include the <i>Watchtower Library</i>,

00:04:36.466 --> 00:04:39.135 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the <i>JW Library</i>® app,

00:04:39.135 --> 00:04:43.765 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the <i>Watchtower ONLINE LIBRARY</i>™<i>,</i>
and the <i>Research Guide.</i>

00:04:45.058 --> 00:04:48.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah wants us to be skillful
in using the tools he has provided

00:04:48.895 --> 00:04:52.857 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so that the proverb
will come true for us that says:

00:04:52.857 --> 00:04:55.986 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
 “Have you seen a man skillful at his work?

00:04:55.986 --> 00:04:58.446 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He will stand before kings.”

00:04:59.865 --> 00:05:02.617 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As you watch the following dramatization,

00:05:02.617 --> 00:05:07.622 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
notice what comes up on Neeta’s Bible study
that challenges her as a teacher,

00:05:07.622 --> 00:05:11.710 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
how she realizes she needs help
to teach effectively,

00:05:11.710 --> 00:05:14.671 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and what research tool she uses

00:05:14.671 --> 00:05:17.549 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to prepare for her study with Jade.

00:05:19.217 --> 00:05:21.219 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
. . . making a friend with God.

00:05:22.471 --> 00:05:24.681 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yeah, I don’t know how to do that.

00:05:24.681 --> 00:05:26.308 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Make a friend?

00:05:26.308 --> 00:05:27.935 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But you’ve done fine with me.

00:05:27.935 --> 00:05:32.397 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But I can see you—but God, a Friend?

00:05:32.397 --> 00:05:33.649 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Seriously?

00:05:33.649 --> 00:05:35.359 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How about what you can see?

00:05:35.359 --> 00:05:38.028 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What does creation teach us about him?

00:05:38.028 --> 00:05:39.822 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Um, not much

00:05:39.822 --> 00:05:43.951 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—maybe evolve or your species dies.

00:05:43.951 --> 00:05:45.410 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It doesn’t really help.

00:05:45.410 --> 00:05:49.873 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, I’m not talking about evolution.

00:05:49.873 --> 00:05:53.836 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m talking about the things
that God has created.

00:05:53.836 --> 00:05:56.505 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You don’t suppose he’s got
a little workshop up there building things

00:05:56.505 --> 00:05:58.549 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
one at a time, do you?

00:05:58.549 --> 00:06:01.260 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the real world, things evolve.

00:06:01.260 --> 00:06:03.804 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s all random.

00:06:03.804 --> 00:06:06.140 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I don’t know what that
tells me about him.

00:06:06.140 --> 00:06:08.475 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I wasn’t ready for this.

00:06:08.475 --> 00:06:10.811 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Evolution isn’t my strong suit.

00:06:12.104 --> 00:06:13.939 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I need help.

00:06:24.241 --> 00:06:26.285 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This could be good:

00:06:26.285 --> 00:06:29.955 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Many who believe evolution. . . 

00:06:29.955 --> 00:06:34.710 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
ancient tidal pool . . . 
chemicals spontaneously assembled . . .”

00:06:34.710 --> 00:06:37.213 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s too deep.

00:06:37.213 --> 00:06:41.717 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Wait!
Maybe: “What does the evidence reveal? . . .

00:06:41.717 --> 00:06:45.054 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“For a cell to survive, . . . DNA . . .

00:06:45.054 --> 00:06:48.057 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“RNA . . . inanimate chemicals. . .

00:06:48.057 --> 00:06:50.184 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
probability . . .”

00:06:50.184 --> 00:06:53.521 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m not sure this is what she needs.

00:06:53.521 --> 00:06:55.565 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Her real issue

00:06:55.565 --> 00:06:58.985 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was getting to know
someone that she can’t see.

00:06:58.985 --> 00:07:01.028 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Maybe that’s the best place to begin.

00:07:07.577 --> 00:07:10.955 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“One widespread false teaching . . .

00:07:10.955 --> 00:07:14.542 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“robs people of hope . . . implies

00:07:14.542 --> 00:07:17.337 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that human life has no purpose . . .”

00:07:17.337 --> 00:07:20.673 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This could be it; establish the positive:

00:07:20.673 --> 00:07:24.010 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What creation really says about Jehovah

00:07:24.010 --> 00:07:27.138 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
versus what evolution obscures.

00:07:27.138 --> 00:07:29.807 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
OK, so you got me thinking, . . .

00:07:29.807 --> 00:07:30.850 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Mm-hm.

00:07:30.850 --> 00:07:32.393 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
. . . and I did some research, . . .

00:07:32.393 --> 00:07:34.187 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
OK. Yeah.

00:07:34.187 --> 00:07:35.855 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
. . . and I think
you’ll really like what I found.

00:07:35.855 --> 00:07:36.856 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
OK.

00:07:36.856 --> 00:07:38.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Come, come, sit down.

00:07:38.525 --> 00:07:39.984 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
OK.

00:07:43.071 --> 00:07:45.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
OK, let’s do this.

00:07:56.084 --> 00:07:58.628 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did you see where Neeta turned for help?

00:07:58.628 --> 00:08:00.630 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The <i>Research Guide.</i>

00:08:00.630 --> 00:08:03.174 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
With a little bit of searching
and persistence,

00:08:03.174 --> 00:08:05.218 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
she found what she needed.

00:08:05.218 --> 00:08:07.721 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
She got excited about the information

00:08:07.721 --> 00:08:10.515 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and passed that excitement on to her student.

00:08:12.476 --> 00:08:16.146 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How can you use
our research tools effectively?

00:08:16.146 --> 00:08:20.233 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You can use them to help you
to explain and teach the Scriptures.

00:08:20.233 --> 00:08:22.402 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
For example, as with Jade,

00:08:22.402 --> 00:08:26.239 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
your students may be struggling
to understand a Scriptural teaching.

00:08:26.239 --> 00:08:30.202 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Or you may have a student
who is trying to overcome a personal problem.

00:08:30.202 --> 00:08:35.082 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Use the tools that Jehovah
has given us to search for an explanation

00:08:35.082 --> 00:08:38.418 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or an illustration that will help the person.

00:08:38.418 --> 00:08:41.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And you may not even have to do
all the work yourself.

00:08:41.797 --> 00:08:45.050 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Perhaps you can show
your students how to use our tools

00:08:45.050 --> 00:08:48.512 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in order to find
the Bible’s answers to their questions.

00:08:50.264 --> 00:08:55.269 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do your best, though,
to learn how to use our research tools.

00:08:55.269 --> 00:08:59.189 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Likely, you already use
<i>JW Library</i> for personal study

00:08:59.189 --> 00:09:03.235 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and family worship and to prepare
for congregation meetings.

00:09:03.235 --> 00:09:08.157 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But if you keep up-to-date
with new features in the <i>JW Library</i> app,

00:09:08.157 --> 00:09:11.619 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you can also use it
to good advantage in your ministry.

00:09:12.745 --> 00:09:16.707 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There are even features
built into the app that make it possible 

00:09:16.707 --> 00:09:19.335 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for you to save the research
that you have done

00:09:19.335 --> 00:09:22.296 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so that you can use it again in the future.

00:09:22.296 --> 00:09:24.590 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What are those features?

00:09:24.590 --> 00:09:27.384 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Notes and tags

00:09:27.384 --> 00:09:29.762 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—notes and tags.

00:09:29.762 --> 00:09:31.764 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Have you learned how to use them?

00:09:31.764 --> 00:09:33.808 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, now you can.

00:09:33.808 --> 00:09:36.519 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If you have <i>JW Library</i> with you on a device,

00:09:36.519 --> 00:09:40.481 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
open the Bible to 1 Timothy chapter 2

00:09:40.481 --> 00:09:42.858 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—1 Timothy chapter 2—

00:09:42.858 --> 00:09:46.279 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and follow along with this tutorial video.

00:09:47.905 --> 00:09:52.076 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are you making full use of <i>JW Library®?</i>

00:09:52.076 --> 00:09:54.579 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Let’s learn how some are using it,

00:09:54.579 --> 00:09:56.664 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
and then practice together.

00:09:56.664 --> 00:10:00.042 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I create notes in my Bible
for many different reasons.

00:10:00.042 --> 00:10:02.253 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It could be a good point from a talk,

00:10:02.253 --> 00:10:06.340 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
an illustration to help me
to explain something to a Bible student,

00:10:06.340 --> 00:10:09.302 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or something for my own meditation.

00:10:09.302 --> 00:10:12.805 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I highlight the key phrase
and create a note.

00:10:12.805 --> 00:10:15.266 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s practice together.

00:10:15.266 --> 00:10:17.602 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If you have <i>JW Library,</i>

00:10:17.602 --> 00:10:21.064 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
find 1 Timothy 2:6 in the Bible.

00:10:22.357 --> 00:10:25.735 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now highlight the word “ransom,”

00:10:25.735 --> 00:10:29.614 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and tap the “Add a note” button.

00:10:32.158 --> 00:10:34.619 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then type your comment.

00:10:38.206 --> 00:10:40.875 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Tapping the note marker in the margin

00:10:40.875 --> 00:10:43.378 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
brings your comment into view.

00:10:43.378 --> 00:10:45.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ve created a lot of notes.

00:10:45.797 --> 00:10:48.591 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I use tags to help me find them again.

00:10:48.591 --> 00:10:52.929 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
For example, whenever I hear a point
that I want to use in the ministry,

00:10:52.929 --> 00:10:55.932 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I create a note and add a tag

00:10:55.932 --> 00:10:59.936 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
like “prayer,” “ransom,” or “last days.”

00:10:59.936 --> 00:11:03.940 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then when I’m in the ministry,
I can quickly find my note.

00:11:03.940 --> 00:11:06.735 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s practice together.

00:11:06.735 --> 00:11:09.321 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
On the note you just created,

00:11:09.321 --> 00:11:11.323 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
tap the three dots

00:11:13.241 --> 00:11:15.619 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
