00:11:23.835 --> 00:11:26.755 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In this case, type “ransom.”

00:11:30.425 --> 00:11:33.387 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You can add as many tags as you like.

00:11:36.723 --> 00:11:38.892 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
To find your notes again,

00:11:38.892 --> 00:11:42.354 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
go to the Personal Study tab.

00:11:42.354 --> 00:11:45.190 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You can type in the Search box,

00:11:45.190 --> 00:11:47.860 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or you can just tap the tag.

00:11:47.860 --> 00:11:50.612 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As I read the Bible chapters
for the midweek meeting,

00:11:50.612 --> 00:11:54.074 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I often come across verses
that I want to understand better.

00:11:54.074 --> 00:11:56.118 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I check the <i>Research Guide.</i>

00:11:56.118 --> 00:11:59.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sometimes I use the points
I find in a comment at the meeting.

00:11:59.621 --> 00:12:02.249 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s practice together.

00:12:02.249 --> 00:12:06.128 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are you still at 1 Timothy chapter 2?

00:12:06.128 --> 00:12:09.465 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Tap on the number for verse 6,

00:12:11.550 --> 00:12:15.262 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
then tap the <i>Research Guide</i> button
on the menu.

00:12:16.889 --> 00:12:20.851 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now you can read information
that explains this verse.

00:12:21.936 --> 00:12:26.524 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You can even copy a portion
of the research and paste it into your note.

00:12:31.028 --> 00:12:35.950 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If you are like me, you will probably
have to watch that video a few more times.

00:12:35.950 --> 00:12:38.077 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If you find it challenging
to learn how to use

00:12:38.077 --> 00:12:40.913 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
some of the features of our tools,
here are two things you can do.

00:12:40.913 --> 00:12:45.334 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
First, ask someone
in your congregation to assist you,

00:12:45.334 --> 00:12:48.796 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and often the young people can help the most.

00:12:48.796 --> 00:12:51.757 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Second, go to jw.org®,

00:12:51.757 --> 00:12:54.302 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
scroll to the bottom of any page,

00:12:54.302 --> 00:12:56.762 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
click on <i>JW Library,</i>

00:12:56.762 --> 00:13:01.767 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and there you will find
more tutorial videos that you can watch.

00:13:03.603 --> 00:13:06.814 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
